name: NISHIKIGOI
description:
Hello everybody!

Here is the fourth piece of JapanCulture, NISHIKIGOI!

The words "koi" and "nishikigoi" come from the Japanese words 鯉 (carp), and 錦鯉 (brocaded carp), respectively.

Nishikigoi meaning in Japan is good fortune or luck. They also are associated with perseverance in adversity and strength of purpose. The Koi fish symbolize good luck, abundance and perseverance. Today the fish are considered to be symbolic of advancement materially and spiritually.

Thank you for reading!
